name: Shredded Scarf No. 1
description:
Hand shredding is a tedious technique performed on everyday cotton t-shirts. Much time is devoted to pulling apart, stretching and revising the fabric to create incredibly soft and airy textures. Perfect for layering during cold months and saving for summer nights…

——————————————————————–

Created from a circular cotton fabric, Scarf No. 1 can be worn many ways…

The solid part (no shredding) is large enough to drape over the head like a hood. Double around neck as a cowl or over the shoulders for a relaxed look – play with it!

Approximate measurements taken while the scarf is relaxed :

Diameter : 70 inches
Solid area width : 19 inches
Shredded area width : 35 inches

*The stretchy quality of this piece allows it’s size to increase when stretched across the body.

100% soft cotton.
Hand colored with fiber reactive dyes, producing permanent results that will not fade.

——————————————————————–

Throughout shredded areas, holes may occur. This is an aspect of the shredded aesthetic and deconstruction technique. To ensure your pieces maintain their look, always hand wash separately and air dry.

Colors may look different from monitor to monitor. In addition, due to the process of hand dyeing – colors vary slightly from one dye bath to the next.

——————————————————————–

Available in 9 colors (excluding “multi”) …
